C69YCogpfY-SfDFAfGT4PSL2tgCLO14zFKgZWcI8=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Java 8 Enum Testing**\\n\\nI’m looking into Java 8 and how to handle enums in a test class. I'm considering using `assertThat(copy).containsEntry`, and I see that `EnumBiMap` extends `Map`, which seems good. There could be potential issues with `ObjectInputStream#readObject`, as it's dynamic-access in the test versus the library. I should explore whether native-image metadata is needed for enum classes, especially regarding serialization. The agent probably generates metadata externally, and we must avoid editing resources.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_2gbyp11kER6a4It61VNXmZ1H|fc_01529b4d6baa70670169fb92a76a64819289fb439a5fde45b1", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0/src/test/java/com_google_collections/google_collections/EnumBiMapTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_google_collections.google_collections;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport com.google.common.collect.EnumBiMap;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class EnumBiMapTest {\n    @Test\n    void serializesEnumKeyAndValueTypesWithEntries() throws Exception {\n        EnumBiMap<SourceStatus, TargetStatus> original = EnumBiMap.create(SourceStatus.class, TargetStatus.class);\n        original.put(SourceStatus.CREATED, TargetStatus.OPEN);\n        original.put(SourceStatus.CLOSED, TargetStatus.DONE);\n\n        EnumBiMap<SourceStatus, TargetStatus> copy = roundTrip(original);\n\n        assertThat(copy).isEqualTo(original);\n        assertThat(copy.keyType()).isSameAs(SourceStatus.class);\n        assertThat(copy.valueType()).isSameAs(TargetStatus.class);\n        assertThat(copy.inverse().get(TargetStatus.OPEN)).isEqualTo(SourceStatus.CREATED);\n        assertThat(copy.inverse().get(TargetStatus.DONE)).isEqualTo(SourceStatus.CLOSED);\n    }\n\n    private static <T> T roundTrip(T object) throws Exception {\n        return deserialize(serialize(object));\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] serialize(Object object) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream output = new ObjectOutputStream(bytes)) {\n            output.writeObject(object);\n        }\n        return bytes.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"unchecked\")\n    private static <T> T deserialize(byte[] bytes) throws Exception {\n        try (ObjectInputStream input = new ObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(bytes))) {\n            return (T) input.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private enum SourceStatus {\n        CREATED,\n        CLOSED\n    }\n\n    private enum TargetStatus {\n        OPEN,\n        DONE\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1077, "output": 918, "cacheRead": 25600, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27595, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778094751070, "responseId": "resp_01529b4d6baa70670169fb929ff5e88192878e53be06dc6218"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_2gbyp11kER6a4It61VNXmZ1H|fc_01529b4d6baa70670169fb92a76a64819289fb439a5fde45b1", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 2155 bytes to tests/src/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0/src/test/java/com_google_collections/google_collections/EnumBiMapTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778094761103}]}
